Hey CMCG folks :wave: Josh here — currently working agency-side as a Digital & SEO strategist with Foundation Marketing. The bulk of my role is content-focused. Internally, I'm leading our blog content, overall organic growth and digital product growth (handful of courses via Podia). Client-side, most of my time spent is upfront building content & SEO strategies for SaaS co's & actually creating the content we're recommending.

Stoked to be a part of this community. Definitely starting to think long-term on the career front more than I have in the past, so can't wait to follow along on & learn from everyone's experiences as well. :rocket:

Hello, hello! 

I'm Kayla. I run a small branding + content marketing agency called Brand Panache, as well as consulting, writing, and creating solo. I have a background in marketing management, startup marketing, agency work, and freelance writing. It's been a mixed bag. Now, I do my own thing. 

Bonus fact: I also read tarot 

I joined for: Inspo/ideas, camaraderie with career peers, mentorship and mentoring others, insight sharing, content swaps, and there's always room for real project collaboration, too. 

I can help with: brand strategy, brand development, culture and EB, naming and color theory, business/product launches, editorial and content planning,  social, and SEO. 

Other interests: Travel, books, yoga, linguistics, nature, creativity, neuroscience, board games, and LEGO

Where to find me: 
Twitter /at/kaylanaab 
LinkedIn /in/kaylanaab
Instagram /at/ whatkayladoes
